The prevalence of asymptomatic transmission doesn't bode well for global containment efforts, as Bill Gates recently wrote in the New England Journal of Medicine.
Of the 3,711 people on board, 712 tested positive, but almost half of them had no symptoms at the time.
Research that examined coronavirus cases in Singapore found that of 157 cases acquired locally, 10 involved presymptomatic transmission.
Research from China in February found that 13% of the 468 confirmed cases studied involved presymptomatic transmission.
Research published March 25 in the journal The Lancet looked at 36 children who tested positive for the coronavirus in three Chinese hospitals.